card.desc: Der MCTS wurde Schritt für Schritt eingeführt und das auch noch sehr  detailliert. Zudem wurden verschiedene Methoden zur Multiprocessing des Algorithmus vorgestellt. Wobei ich mich in meiner Arbeit auf die einfachste beschränke, weil die anderen wahrscheinlich den Rahmen sprängen und zu viel RAM benötigen. Ich werde root-paralellisierung verwenden, das heisst ich starte einfach mehrere Instanzen des mcts und lasse diese einzeln rechnen. So kann ich mehre self-play Spiele gleichzeitig erzeugen.

card.desc: Der eigentliche Algorithmus funktioniert wie folgt: man Initialisiert ein Neuronales Netz mit “random-weights” und benutzt dieses in der simulation-phase des mcts um eine Schätzung über den Spielausgang zu erhalten. Der beste Zug wird dann gespielt und das wird wiederholt, bis das Spielbrett voll ist. Die erhaltenen Spieldaten (Spielzustand, (Zug-Wahrscheinlichkeiten des MCTS, Spielausgang)) werden dann benutzt um das neuronale Netzwerk zu trainieren. Dieses wird dann in der nächsten Iteration zur Spielausgangsschätzung verrwendet.

listing.description:
Sync Trello cards with Excel rows using this powerful integration.

---

## Sync information from Trello into Excel and get real-time insights on project performance
With Unito, sync Trello cards to rows in Excel and keep everything updated automatically. Build powerful reports in Excel to get insights on progress in Trello with no manual work.

Unito also supports 2-way workflows, which means changes made in Excel are synced back to your Trello cards. You can also use Unito to automatically create new Trello cards when a new row is created in Excel. Unito helps keep everything in perfect sync across any workflow that needs Excel and Trello.

![Trello - Excel Integration](https://unito.io/wp-content/uploads/2022/05/TrelloExcel.mp4.gif)

## Features
### Supports essential Trello fields
Unito has some of the deepest two-way integrations for Trello. Sync card names, due dates, assignees, card status, card descriptions, labels, list names, board names, and more. You can manually map these fields with any Excel column and keep your data in sync.

### Customize in real-time
Unito integrations allow data to flow across tools in real-time. Customize your flow to your exact needs and set powerful filters to define what you need synced. Make changes to your flow and they’ll be reflected in your tools in real-time.

### No-code and self-serve

# Statuses 💥
Yep, that’s exactly what you are thinking of – the tool to keep your workflow’s statuses up to date, organized, and transparent!

![Status creation](https://card-status.nyc3.cdn.digitaloceanspaces.com/images/store/status-creation.webp)

Statuses are not related to Trello lists and do not depend on them (you can keep cards with a variety of statuses in one Trello list).

![Status settings](https://card-status.nyc3.cdn.digitaloceanspaces.com/images/store/status-settings.png)

**Default List** – сhange statuses with just a swipe! Yeah, as easy as it sounds!
The default list can be set from the status settings – select any list in a board you want. Then, any card that appears in that list will have status and actions applied to it.

**Easy Switch** – we understand that working with complicated processes is not easy. That's why we introduce a painkiller – Easy Switch!
Select as many statuses as you want to be listed as Card Buttons so that you can switch to that statuses right from a card view by simply pressing a Button. You are welcome to specify a unique set of easy-switch statuses for each status.

**Description** – want to leave a note for teammates? – Description is the tool!

Automation that is triggered on a card when you select a status – we call it Action. We prepared a lot of them!

- Ask member to select due date on Status selection;
- Remove due date;
- Mark due date as (in)complete.

Members automation (on Status selection):

listing.description:
🎉 Statuses & Workflow is [one of the FASTEST GROWING](https://www.bluecatreports.com/blog/power-up-stats-2023) power-ups of 2023 🎉

# Manage statuses and workflow with ease 🧞‍♂️

💙 FREE to go
💡 Fits any team and process
⚡️ Easy to set up
🤖 Advanced PRO features

![Demo](https://card-status.nyc3.cdn.digitaloceanspaces.com/images/store/demo.webp)

## What is it about?
Statuses & Workflow provides an ultimate solution for Statuses and Workflow management: it makes your process intuitive and easy to follow – this is exactly what you’ve been waiting for! Not only does it maintain the Workflow of your Trello board, but it can do handy *automation* for you, like moving a card to a specific list, managing card members, setting due date, completing checklists, and doing whatever you want with joy. The best part is that the product has been in active development all this time, and we still have a lot of features to implement, stay tuned! 😉

![How does it work?](https://card-status.nyc3.cdn.digitaloceanspaces.com/images/store/how-it-works.gif)

🧡 Statuses & Workflow is designed and developed by ThunderModules – fastest growing new publisher of 2022 🧡

## Enhance your workflow with our solutions!
Try [Card Done](https://trello.com/power-ups/6244a5a256399f22036820cb) to complete your Trello cards in just one click ✅
Try [Tables & Spreadsheets](https://trello.com/power-ups/65c7808c749e34145008f9b4) to create tables directly within your Trello cards 🦖

---

# Statuses 💥
Yep, that’s exactly what you are thinking of – the tool to keep your workflow’s statuses up to date, organized, and transparent!

![Status creation](https://card-status.nyc3.cdn.digitaloceanspaces.com/images/store/status-creation.webp)

Create, update, and drag & drop your Statuses, set up unique to your team flow with special colors and icons. We also support Status enabling|disabling and the ability to hide a Status from a card’s front side. Statuses are not related to Trello lists and do not depend on them (you can keep cards with a variety of statuses in one Trello list).

![Status settings](https://card-status.nyc3.cdn.digitaloceanspaces.com/images/store/status-settings.png)

**Default List** – сhange statuses with just a swipe! Yeah, as easy as it sounds!
The default list can be set from the status settings – select any list in a board you want. Then, any card that appears in that list will have status and actions applied to it.

**Easy Switch** – we understand that working with complicated processes is not easy. That's why we introduce a painkiller – Easy Switch!
Select as many statuses as you want to be listed as Card Buttons so that you can switch to that statuses right from a card view by simply pressing a Button. You are welcome to specify a unique set of easy-switch statuses for each status.

**Description** – want to leave a note for teammates? – Description is the tool! 
It's visible in a status header on the Statuses page and improves onboarding with your custom notes about status usage. Members can hover over a description to get into the process.

# Actions 🤖
Automation that is triggered on a card when you select a status – we call it Action. We prepared a lot of them!

![Dates-members-labels](https://card-status.nyc3.cdn.digitaloceanspaces.com/images/store/actions-dates-members-labels.png)

### Dates Actions 🗓
Always wanted to keep your team accountable for timelines? Add due dates to cards based on Status.

Due date automation (on Status selection):
- Set due date to now;
- Set due date on a specific date or in a particular timeline;
- Ask member to select due date on Status selection;
- Remove due date;
- Mark due date as (in)complete.

### Members Actions 👥
Assign work on specific members based on a card Status!

Members automation (on Status selection):
- Remove|add all members from|to a card;
- Remove|add status changer from|to a card;
- Remove|add particular members from|to a card;

### Labels Actions 🏷
Nearly-native way to keep the right labels assigned to the right cards! You can select to remove all labels from a card or to add a specific set of labels. Either way, we keep labels up to date with your board settings so no need to update labels in the power-up settings.

### Checklists and Other Actions ✅
![Move-comment-checklists](https://card-status.nyc3.cdn.digitaloceanspaces.com/images/store/actions-move-comment-checklists.png)

Automating checklists can be annoying, that’s why we put additional effort to make them easy to setup and use.

Checklists automation (on Status selection):
- Add a new checklist with checklists to a card;
- Complete a checklist in a card, also you can select to complete all checklists in a card;
- Remove a checklist in a card, remove all checklists in a card;
More to come!

### Other Actions
Smaller, but still useful actions:

- **Comment** – designed to automatically leave a comment in a card, you can also ask member to leave a comment during status selection;
- **Move** – it moves a card to a selected list in your workspace (any public board);
- **Remove** – allows you to archive or delete a card on status selection;

# Analytics 📊
What's an average time per status? Which statuses are used most frequently? Do you want to dive deeper into the data?

Four amazing charts to help you in the investigation!
![Analytics demo](https://card-status.nyc3.cdn.digitaloceanspaces.com/images/store/analytics.png)

**Statuses Now Chart** – сards with statuses currently on your board. It’s as simple as that! Helps to understand the current state of a board and the cards in it. You can filter that chart by status to hide some of them.

**Timeline Chart** is designed to show the average time per status and identify potential blockers in your process. Use it to make your workflow smoother! BTW, you can filter that chart by a time range to see how the timeline has changed over time.

**Usage Chart** – want to know which statuses are used most frequently? Statuses Usage is the tool for you! Check how many statuses have been applied, which ones, and when. Maybe it’s time to groom rarely-used statuses or even let them go.

**Transitions Chart** – if you want to investigate a status or learn more about its’ transitions, try the Transitions chart! Simply select a status to analyze and view all the transitions In and Out!

---

# Pricing
The power-up is FREE forever.

PRO subscription pricing is **1.99 USD/month** per unique member on all connected boards within a workspace.
*With a minimum of 3.98 USD per workspace. And maximum of 19.9 USD.*

*Note:*

* We support enterprise – shoot us an email at cardstatus@thundermodules.com
* Yearly-based subscription can be provided on demand. With an addition discount.
* We have additional discounts for non-profits.
* Only workspace members can manage power-up and subscription.

---

# Roadmap
We are excited to continue working on Statuses & Workflow power up and here is **the plan**:

![Roadmap](https://card-status.nyc3.cdn.digitaloceanspaces.com/images/store/roadmap.png)

**We will add new features as soon as they are tested and ready to go**. Also, the priority of features depends on your feedback. In this way, we can learn from you, analyze your interest in the Statuses & Workflow power-up, and grow wisely with excellent quality!

If you want to help us deliver faster, please share the power-up with your fellows!

## Let’s talk!
[![Feedback](https://card-status.nyc3.cdn.digitaloceanspaces.com/images/store/customer-interview.png)](https://xzlp910bk4i.typeform.com/to/BIUvtD34?utm_source=store-page&utm_campaign=public-beta)

Have feedback? Found a bug? Looking for support? Interested in a partnership? Good start!
Shoot us an email at cardstatus@thundermodules.com

## Release history
- 1.4.2: Minor bug fixes, stabilization improvements *(May 2024)* 🛠

listing.name: API Developer ID Helper
listing.description:
The API Developer ID Helper Power-Up allows Trello API Developers easy access to the technical IDs of a Trello Board (Board ID, List ID, and Card ID), instead of the rather cumbersome "[Export to JSON](https://youtu.be/aWYEg1wPVYY)" method.

## Copy Card Data
Get CardId and the other various IDs on a card (ListId, CardId, Member IDs, Label Ids and Checklist Ids), or the entire Card JSON directly from the Card-Button in your clipboard

![Card Features](https://ambitious-moss-04a010603.3.azurestaticapps.net/card2.gif)

## Copy List Data
Get ListId or the List with Card JSON from the List "..." dropdown menu in your clipboard

![List Features](https://ambitious-moss-04a010603.3.azurestaticapps.net/list2.gif)

## Copy Board Data
Get BoardId, the Board as JSON, WorkSpace ID, the Member Ids and Label Ids from the Board-Button to your your clipboard

![Board Features](https://ambitious-moss-04a010603.3.azurestaticapps.net/board2.gif)

## Settings
By default, the Info buttons are shown to all users, but if you like you can hide them for all users and then personally override that the buttons should be shown to you only:

![Settings](https://ambitious-moss-04a010603.3.azurestaticapps.net/settings.png)

## Version History

### Version 3.0 (14th of September 2024)
#### Board Button
- Added Support for Custom Field Ids

### Version 2.0 (19th of June 2024)
#### General
- New and better design
- Settings and now general for the board with the option to do a person override
- Trello Notification when ID is copied

#### Board Button
- Labels, Members and WorkSpace ID are now possible to copy
- Now show when the board was created

#### List Button
- Can now show IDs for each card in a list
- Now show when the list was created

#### Card Button
- Labels, Members and Checklist IDs are now possible to copy
- Now show when the card was created

### Version 2.0 (19th of June 2024)
#### General
- New and better design
- Settings and now general for the board with the option to do a person override
- Trello Notification when ID is copied

#### Board Button
- Labels, Members and WorkSpace ID are now possible to copy
- Now show when the board was created

#### List Button
- Can now show IDs for each card in a list
- Now show when the list was created

#### Card Button
- Labels, Members and Checklist IDs are now possible to copy
- Now show when the card was created

### Version 1.0 (2nd of June 2023)
- Initial Release

## Support
If you need help with anything, feel free to reach out to rasmus.wulff.jensen@gmail.com or submit a [github-issue](https://github.com/rwjdk/trello-developer-power-up/issues).

listing.name: OneDrive
listing.description:
Mit dem OneDrive-Power-Up für Trello landen Ihre Dateien und Ordner direkt auf Ihren Trello-Karten. Navigieren Sie mithilfe der Dateiauswahl direkt von Trello aus in OneDrive, um wichtige Dateien anzuhängen. Kopieren Sie Links zu OneDrive-Ordnern auf Trello-Karten, um Ordner anzuhängen. Erhalten Sie eine Vorschau und die neuesten Details sowie Links, mit denen Sie direkt zu OneDrive gelangen, wo Sie Dokumente bearbeiten und auf Dateien zugreifen können.

- Hängen Sie mithilfe der integrierten Dateiauswahl Dateien von OneDrive an eine Trello-Karte an.
- Kopieren Sie Links einfach von einem OneDrive-Ordner oder hängen Sie Ordner über das Anhangsmenü an Karten an.
- Erhalten Sie eine Vorschau für an Karten angehängte OneDrive-Dateien sowie Details zu Erstellungszeit und -datum und zum letzten Änderungszeitpunkt.
- Funktioniert mit OneDrive for Business und OneDrive Personal

### Screenshot

![Kartenrückseite OneDrive-Bereich](https://onedrive.trello.services/images/onedrive-screenshot.png)

listing.name: Karte zurückstellen
listing.description:
Zurückstellen bedeutet erhalten.

Jetzt können Sie die Karten ordnen, die Sie erst zu einem späteren Zeitpunkt bearbeiten werden. Mit dem Power-Up „Karte zurückstellen” können Sie eine Karte für einen späteren Zeitpunkt zurückstellen. Dann erscheint sie später von selbst wieder auf dem Board. Benötigen Sie sie früher? Sie finden Ihre Karte unter „archivierte“ Karten.

- Stellen Sie eine Karte auf ein bestimmtes Datum oder eine bestimmte Zeit zurück.
- Die Karte erscheint dann von selbst wieder. Simsalabim!

![Screenshot](https://card-snooze.trello.services/images/Card_Snooze_1.jpg)
![Screenshot](https://card-snooze.trello.services/images/Card_Snooze_2.jpg)
listing.overview: Stellen Sie eine Karte zurück (bzw. archivieren Sie sie) bis zu einem bestimmten Zeitpunkt, an dem sie auf dem Board wiederhergestellt wird.

listing.name: Kalender-Power-Up
listing.description:
Erhalten Sie einen Überblick über Fälligkeitsdaten mit dem Kalender-Power-Up für Trello. Egal, ob Sie eine Konferenz planen, einen Redaktionskalender verwalten oder einen Familienurlaub planen: Mit dem Kalender-Power-Up können Sie Karten mit Fälligkeitsdaten in einer wöchentlichen oder monatlichen Kalenderansicht anzeigen. Priorisieren Sie Karten ganz einfach, indem Sie sie in den Kalender ziehen und dort ablegen, um ihre Fälligkeitsdaten automatisch zu aktualisieren. Exportieren Sie Ihren Trello-Kalender an Apps von Drittanbietern mithilfe eines iCalendar-Links.

- Präsentieren und filtern Sie Karten mit Fälligkeitsdatum in einer Wochen- oder Monatskalenderansicht.

- Verwalten Sie Fälligkeitsdaten, indem Sie Karten in den Kalender ziehen und dort ablegen.

- Sie erkennen erledigte Aufgaben einfach, indem Sie Fälligkeitsdaten als erledigt markieren.

- Exportieren Sie den Kalender eines Boards an Kalender von Drittanbietern mithilfe des eindeutigen iCalendar-Links eines Boards.

- Das Kalender Power-Up wird im Internet sowie auf iOS- und Android-Mobilgeräten unterstützt.

cards.desc: Der MCTS wurde Schritt für Schritt eingeführt und das auch noch sehr  detailliert. Zudem wurden verschiedene Methoden zur Multiprocessing des Algorithmus vorgestellt. Wobei ich mich in meiner Arbeit auf die einfachste beschränke, weil die anderen wahrscheinlich den Rahmen sprängen und zu viel RAM benötigen. Ich werde root-paralellisierung verwenden, das heisst ich starte einfach mehrere Instanzen des mcts und lasse diese einzeln rechnen. So kann ich mehre self-play Spiele gleichzeitig erzeugen.
cards.name: Literatur lesen zum MCTS und multiprocessing

cards.desc: Fazit nach dem Lesen: Die Standfordgruppe hat ziemlich den gleichen Algorithmus implementiert und das auhc für Othello. Für 30 Iterationen haben sie etwa 72h gebraucht, wobei ihre Hardware schlechter war als meine, die ich jetzt verwenden kann. Ausserdem gaben sie nochmals eine Zusammenfassung über den Algorithmus, was mich in meinem Wissen bestärkt. Zudem ist guter demo-code angehängt, welchen man sich anschauen kann.
cards.name: Literatur lesen: Othello Zero (Standford Arbeit)

cards.desc: Der eigentliche Algorithmus funktioniert wie folgt: man Initialisiert ein Neuronales Netz mit “random-weights” und benutzt dieses in der simulation-phase des mcts um eine Schätzung über den Spielausgang zu erhalten. Der beste Zug wird dann gespielt und das wird wiederholt, bis das Spielbrett voll ist. Die erhaltenen Spieldaten (Spielzustand, (Zug-Wahrscheinlichkeiten des MCTS, Spielausgang)) werden dann benutzt um das neuronale Netzwerk zu trainieren. Dieses wird dann in der nächsten Iteration zur Spielausgangsschätzung verrwendet.
